about.summary: Contains a number of common astronomy conversion routines, particularly the HMS and degrees schemes, which can be fiddly to convert between on mass due to the textural nature of the former. It allows users to coordinate match datasets quickly. It also contains functions for various cosmological calculations.

name: r-celestial
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.4.6" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-celestial
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  fn: celestial_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/celestial_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/celestial/celestial_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9f647f41465ac65b254717698f1978871c378ad8e6ccaa693abf579437069abe

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-nistunits
    - r-rann
    - r-pracma
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-nistunits
    - r-rann
    - r-pracma

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('celestial')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('celestial')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=celestial
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Contains a number of common astronomy conversion routines, particularly the HMS and
    degrees schemes, which can be fiddly to convert between on mass due to the textural
    nature of the former. It allows users to coordinate match datasets quickly. It also
    contains functions for various cosmological calculations.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
    - dbast
    - npavlovikj
